Abuja – Armed security operatives have taken over the popular unity fountain in Abuja to stop  #RevolutionNow protest slated for today, Monday. A combined team of anti riot policemen, soldiers and airforce personnel were stationed at strategic positions at the Fountain and feyderal Secretariat to disrupt the planned protest. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Also, amoured personnel carriers (APCs) and water canons were stationed around the Eagle Square. The protesters have not shown up at as time of filling this report. Organisers of the protest had earlier assured that the protest would continue nationwide despite the arrest of its convener, Omoyele Sowore. Details later…